<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="766" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="58.[2078,2669,1550,1973]" pageId="58" pageNumber="766">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2078,2355,1748,1777]" pageId="58" pageNumber="766">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body c.68-72 mm, tail ¢.62-67 mm; weight mean 13-5 g. The Lesser Pygmy Flying Squirrel is the smallest flying squirrel. Cheeks are pale buff, ventral surfaceis white, and dorsal fur is dark rufous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
